        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 2:55PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 255 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles northwest of Golden, or 19 miles northwest of Mineola, moving
northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Winnsboro, Quitman, Pleasant Grove, Golden, Forest Hill, Alba and
Yantis.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
